"The degree of technology exploitation in healthcare varies widely. There are many reasons why certain areas of healthcare seem to be resistant to digital progress. These range from the technical and economic to the political and emotional. Fortunately, there are some practical solutions that can mitigate several of the major problems and allow progress. These solutions originate from the domain of network security. We can look to the web for inspiration, with its massive store of content and functionality. What's needed is a suite of scalable, network-based identity and security services. Richie Saville of Flexeye argues that this will result in medical practitioners gaining a better view of their patients. There are many improvements that could be made to healthcare systems that would give medical practitioners a better view and understanding of their patients. And some of the most interesting derive from the world of network security."
